# Personal pre-commit markers — strings the hook must never let into a commit.
#
# Copy this file to markers.local (gitignored) and add your own, ONE REGEX PER LINE:
# employer or product names, your username, internal hostnames, etc. Keeping them
# here (out of the public repo) means the guard works without publishing the very
# strings it protects.
#
# Lines starting with # and blank lines are ignored. Matching is case-insensitive
# (grep -i). Put real values in markers.local, NOT in this tracked example.
#
# Examples (replace with your own in markers.local):
# acme-corp
# my-username
# internal\.example\.tld
